Comment (src/views/control-implementations/partials/StatementByComponent.vue:270):
**Low (a11y) — duplicate DOM ids.** `id="by-component-status"` (and `by-component-status-remarks` below) are static, but this component is rendered once per by-component inside `ControlStatementByComponents`' `v-for`. With two components in edit mode at the same time, the page has duplicate ids and the `<Label for>` association targets only the first one. Suggest deriving the ids from the component, e.g. `:id=\`by-component-status-${byComponent.uuid}\``, with the matching `for` on the labels.
Replies:
**lisa implementation guidance:** In src/views/control-implementations/partials/StatementByComponent.vue, replace the static edit-mode ids by deriving stable unique ids from byComponent.uuid. Add constants/computed values near the other edit-state helpers, for example statusInputId = computed(() => `by-component-status-${byComponent.uuid}`) and statusRemarksInputId = computed(() => `by-component-status-remarks-${byComponent.uuid}`). Bind the Label and control pairs with :for/:id for both the status Select and remarks Textarea. Do not use the v-for index, because the component only receives the byComponent and the uuid is the stable identifier.

